Class ModelFlashCardDeck

  • java.lang.Object
    • ModelFlashCardDeck
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ModelFlashCardDeck
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Author:
    Trinh Nguyen
    Description: Class that stores multiple ModelFlashCard objects, the cards are managed using the Queue model. Cards are added, removed, and manipulated using queue and dequeue methods.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • removeAll

        public void removeAll()
        Empties the deck by running dequeue() until there is no more cards left. The deck still exist in memory in case more cards are being added.
        Complexity: O(N).

      • enqueueBacktoNext

        public void enqueueBacktoNext()
        Used by other classes to make enqueue(ModelFlashCard) the current card and dequeue() until it is the card after next in line. Often used when switching between main deck and memorized deck.
        Complexity: O(N).

      • enqueueBacktoPrevious

        public void enqueueBacktoPrevious()
        Used by other classes to enqueue(ModelFlashCard) until the next card is the previous card of the current card. Used by the previous card JButton.
        Complexity: O(N).

      • replaceCard

        public void replaceCard(ModelFlashCard card)

        Complexity: O(N).

      • deleteCard

        public void deleteCard(int ID)
